post_text: Attention: MHS and MMS physical and athletic paperwork packets are ready to be picked up at the field house. They will be, on a table, just inside the front doors. They can be picked up this week Wed-Fri from 8:30am to 7pm. All incoming 7th graders, anyone who has never had an athletic physical, or those that answer yes to the specific questions, on the medical history, are required to get a physical. All other students and parents must fill out the entire packet and return to Coach Acosta, Coach Brown, or Coach Woodard by the first day of practice. If you have any questions contact Coach Acosta

post_text:
Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.
P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

text: McISD and Rankin ISD will make a decision Saturday evening concerning school closure.

post_text:
Public Information

The top priority of Rankin ISD and McCamey ISD is providing a safe environment for our students, staff, and families. We understand there are health concerns over the recent outbreak of respiratory illness caused by the new coronavirus called COVID-19.

Rankin ISD, McCamey ISD, and all local representatives in Upton County are closely monitoring the situation and tracking information provided by local, state, and national healthcare providers. As of now, there is no indication of an immediate threat to the Rankin and McCamey communities.

Both Rankin ISD and McCamey ISD will resume classes on March 16th as normal, unless otherwise mandated by the Texas Education Agency, CDC, or Texas Commissioner of Education. These decisions are based on emphasizing facts over fear and relying on credible sources for information.

Ronnie Golson
McCamey ISD Superintendent
Sammy Wyatt
Rankin ISD Superintendent

post_text: Great group of young student athletes!
shared_text:
Amy Acosta is with Kelsey Fillmon and 15 others.
October 6, 2019 at 10:46 AM ¬∑

The last Saturday Cross Country meet with these awesome kiddos. The next one will be their District meet on Monday, Oct 14th.

These kids compete week after week in a sport that not many will ever attend to watch. They wake up to go to 6am practices. They don‚Äôt get the praise or the glory that other athletes get for their sport. But they do it. And they are building this sport one year at at time. They may not be the best team out there.....yet......but they work at it every day to improve. They run to represent their school and they run to represent their community. I think they are amazing. And it has been an honor to spend these Saturdays with them.
(Still missing a few from this pic)
#3TRPS #thefoundation
